&lt;p&gt;At Circle, we are passionate about delivering innovation and excellence in healthcare - principles which are at the heart of diagnostics service. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Consultant Radiologist to join our Diagnostics team with a mission to make healthcare better for patients. The post holder will be expected to provide a general radiological service comprising of MRI, ultrasound, fluoroscopy and plain film reporting. A subspecialty interest in MSK, would be actively encouraged and there is great scope for this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have full GMC registration with a licence to practice and be eligible for inclusion on the Specialist Register or be within 6 months of obtaining your CCT at the time of interview and hold appropriate medical degrees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(10 sessions per week; 8 clinical and 2 SPA).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Option of part-time or pro-rata work will be considered for the appropriate candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Package includes pension, private health insurance and study leave).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
